net.dean.jraw.pagination

Class Contribution

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.dean.jraw.models.JsonModel
      • net.dean.jraw.models.RedditObject
        • net.dean.jraw.models.core.Thing
          • net.dean.jraw.pagination.Contribution

  • public class Contribution
extends Thing
    This class functions as a "hacky" way to have more than one return type for UserContributionPaginator, which will return both Submissions and Comments. This class will mirror the Submission's or Comment's fullname, ID, and type. It is recommended to discard this object as soon as possible in favor of using getSubmission() or getComment(). To determine whether this class is wrapping a Submission or a Comment, use contribution.getType() == ThingType.SUBMISSION or contribution.getType() == net.dean.jraw.models.ThingType.COMMENT

      • data

        public <T> T data(java.lang.String name,
                  java.lang.Class<T> type)
        Description copied from class: JsonModel
        Retrieves a value from the JSON node (provided in the constructor) of type T. When the class is Boolean, Double, Integer, Long, Float, or String, then it returns one of those objects using JsonNode.asX(). If class is URI, or URI, a new URL or URI is returned. If class is (java.util.)Date, then the JsonNode's value is assumed to be long. The value is multiplied by 1000 (since the value is assumed to be in seconds) and then passed to Date.Date(long). Finally, if the class is RenderStringPair, then one will be returned based on the value of JrawConfig.loadRenderStringPairHtml
        Overrides:
        data in class JsonModel
        Type Parameters:
        T - The desired return data type
        Parameters:
        name - The key to look up in the JSON node.
        type - The wanted return value. Supported values are any class representing a primitive data type, such as Integer or Boolean.
        Returns:
        An object of type T in the JSON node
